            <sentence>
                <offset>817</offset>
                <text>Craniofacial findings included relative macrocephaly (OFC 55 cm; 90th percentile), frontal bossing, hypertelorism (inner canthal distance 3.5 cm; &gt;97th percentile – outer canthal distance 11 cm; &gt;97th percentile), down slant of palpebral fissures, short nose with anteverted nostrils, wide philtrum and thin upper lip.</text>
